Injecting CSS to the Tana app
#
Find this file within the Tana.app build by right-clicking on the app and choosing Show Contents: macOS Applications Tana.app Contents Resources app build preload.js
Add the following line of code:
window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => { const style = document.createElement('style'); style.textContent = ` /* Paste your CSS here */ `; document.head.appendChild(style); console.log('Custom CSS injected as inline style.'); });
And replace the / Paste your CSS here / with your entire stylesheet worth of code.
That's the simplest method, recently discovered by Lasse Be Furustad
There's a more advanced method discovered by Andre Foeken that involves using different injection code but allows you to use an entire sheet, but you have to store it locally and run a local web server.
You'll need to update your code and this file on every new app release of Tana, so I suggest setting up a VSC workspace that houses your code and a link to this .js doc so you can easily refresh it each time with a simple copy/paste/reload.
Helped Adam G with tana: https://tanacommunity.slack.com/archives/C055K8L3FMK/p1749750515027549
